3.1 External Interface Requirements\par
3.1.1 User Interfaces\par
The following screens will be provided:\par
Login screen: This will be the first screen that will be displayed. It allows user to access\par
different screens based upon the user role. Various fields available on this screen will be\par
User id: alphanumeric of length up to 10char.\par
Password: alphanumeric of length up to 10char\par
Role: Will have the following\par
Values: Administrator, Data entry Operator , student , teacher\par
2) Subject info Parameter Screen:\par
This screen will be accessible only to the Administrator. It will allow the user to enter the\par
semester number for which the user wants to access the subject information.\par
3) Student info Parameter Screen:\par
This screen will be accessible only to the Administrator. It will allow the user to enter the\par
Batch Year for which the user wants to access the student information.\par
4) Student Information Screen: This screen will be accessible only to the Administrator.\par
It will allow the user to modify the information about new/existing student for particular\par
batch year. Various fields available on these screen are:\par
Student Enrollment No: of the format B.E/YYYY where YYYY represents the batch year\par
Student Name: only alphabetic letters and length up to 40 chars.\par
Batch Year: of the format YYYY\par
5) Marks Entry Parameter Screen: This screen will be accessible only to the Teacher. It\par
will allow the user to enter the Batch Year, the semester number and the subject for\par
which the user wants to access the marks information.\par
6) Marks entry screen: Screen: This screen will be accessible only to the Teacher. It will\par
